He is adding a new element for the array without overwriting the current elements, so with the const todos, he is referring to all elements for the array

setTodos([...todos, NEW ARRAY ELEMENT])

In this case, a new array element is an object

for example, using the rest operator you can copy arrays

let myArr = [25, 50, 35];

let myArrCopy = [...myArr];

// ====
myArrCopy = [50, ...myArr];
here you can add a new element in the first position of the array
